    <note>Lian(2) Guangyu [21792] He once held office as Yingshan county magistrate, where he was buried and his family settled. His descendant, Nanfu [21800] (q.v.) was buried in Fuzhou, Huaian county, which may have been the ancestral home, but the earliest Fuzhou jinshi was a 999 jinshi from Minxian (Sanshan zhi, 26.7b), which I identify as ancestral address; funerary inscription for grandson, Shunbin [21794], only indicates that Guangyu moved from Min (Fujian).</note>
